headline: How Control of the Senate Came Down to Two Georgia Runoffs
text: In the days since Joseph R. Biden Jr. was declared the winner in the presidential contest, the vote counting and reporting in states across the country have continued and are helping to clarify what the Senate will look like in 2021.
snippet: The Democrats had expected to flip several seats, but came up short. Their hopes to control the chamber now rest on a pair of races in Georgia.
